      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on the full pedicle screw-rod construct. Stiffness QoI changes by 1.1% between medium (approx. 180k elements) and fine (approx. 620k elements) meshes. Grid Convergence Index (GCI) computed as 2.3%, well below 5% threshold. Discretization error adequately controlled."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Nonlinear solver residuals converge to < 1e-5 for all load steps. Energy convergence criterion met.",
      "rationale": "Newton-Raphson nonlinear solver converges to force residual norm < 1e-6 and displacement residual norm < 1e-5 for all 120 load increments across all 11 model instances. No divergence or line-search failures observed. Numerical solver error controlled at required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of model setup, boundary conditions, and material assignments completed by analyst not involved in primary model construction.",
      "rationale": "An independent FDA OSEL analyst reviewed all model setup files, boundary condition definitions, and material property assignments against the documented modeling protocol. One minor discrepancy (incorrect screw head diameter in one instance) was identified and corrected prior to final simulation runs. Use error controls adequate at level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elastic-plastic constitutive model with isotropic hardening demonstrated to be appropriate for Ti-6Al-4V pedicle screw under quasi-static compression-bending. Justification supported by literature and material characterization data.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening model for Ti-6Al-4V calibrated against uniaxial tensile coupon data (E=114 GPa, sigma_y=880 MPa, tangent modulus=1.2 GPa). Literature review confirms this model form is standard practice for quasi-static spinal implant FEA. Thread geometry is explicitly modeled; no thread-stripping failure mode is expected under the applied load range. Model form adequately justified at level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All material properties and geometric parameters derived from traceable measurements or certified material data sheets. Uncertainty in key inputs (E, sigma_y) quantified.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V material properties sourced from lot-specific tensile test certificates (n=5 coupons per lot). Geometric dimensions measured via CMM on representative screws (n=3 per lot). Coefficient of friction for screw-rod interface determined from dedicated tribology tests (mu = 0.12 ± 0.03). Parametric sensitivity analysis confirms stiffness QoI is most sensitive to elastic modulus (±2.1% per ±1% change in E). Model inputs documented and traceable at level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 test constructs from production-representative lots tested across at least two independent laboratories.",
      "rationale": "N=11 pedicle screw constructs (non-cannulated, 7.5 mm diameter, standard length) assembled from production lots and tested across two independent laboratories (FDA OSEL and DePuy Synthes in-house lab). Construct dimensions verified by CMM prior to testing. Sample sizes and laboratory diversity meet level 3 requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading scenarios; at minimum two distinct test configurations or load levels evaluated.",
      "rationale": "Testing was performed under a single ASTM F1717 compression-bending configuration (5° offset, 10 mm/min crosshead speed, ambient temperature). While this configuration is the regulatory standard, only one test condition was evaluated. Multiple load levels or angular offsets were not explored. Achieved level 2 is below required level 3; this gap is acknowledged and accepted given the regulatory context of ASTM F1717 as the sole required configuration."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model input parameters (geometry, material, boundary conditions) demonstrably equivalent to test specimen parameters within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "CMM-measured screw and rod dimensions were used directly as model geometry inputs (deviations < 0.05 mm from nominal). Material properties for each model instance were assigned from the corresponding lot-specific test certificate. Boundary conditions (fixture grip length, offset distance) replicate F1717 fixture geometry to within 0.1 mm. Equivalency of inputs confirmed at level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval < 1.96 and percent difference < 10% for all three primary QoIs.",
      "rationale": "All three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) satisfy E/uval < 1.96 and percent difference < 10%. Stiffness: 4.2% diff, E/uval=0.83. Yield force: 6.8% diff, E/uval=1.41. Force at 40 mm: 7.3% diff, E/uval=1.62. Quantitative output comparison meets level 3 requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to the COU decision criteria and reflect clinically meaningful failure modes.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load sharing with the spine; yield force and force at 40 mm displacement are the regulatory acceptance metrics in ASTM F1717. These QoIs are directly used in the 510(k) submission decision. Relevance of QoIs to COU is fully established at level 3."
    },
    {
