  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/decision/cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/actor/credibility-team-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted given that ASTM F1717 specifies a single canonical test configuration for regulatory submissions and the model has demonstrated robust predictive accuracy across all three QoIs. The methodology described in Nagaraja et al. (2024), referenced via DOI 10.1016/j.ymeth.2024.03.003, provides the statistical framework underpinning the E/uval acceptance criterion applied here. Overall credibility is sufficient to support a Medium assurance level decision for the non-cannulated pedicle screw 510(k) submission.",
